{
  "texts": [
    "MethodsSince this research did not involve human participants, ethical approval was not required.",
    "A total of 23 questions, comprising 9 dichotomous and 14 open-ended questions (Table 1), were developed based on the \"Clinical Considerations for a Regenerative Procedure\" guideline provided by the AAE [23] (Fig. 1).",
    "These questions were designed to potentially guide clinicians in performing clinical RET procedures.",
    "Anticipating that responses from AI tools may vary depending on the phrasing of questions, context, or timing, we adopted a systematic approach in formulating the questions as outlined below.• Question Design: All questions were developed based on the 2022 guidelines of the American Association of Endodontists (AAE), ensuring scientific accuracy and clinical relevance.",
    "• Clinical Relevance: Questions focused on practical aspects of regenerative endodontic treatment (RET), such as procedural feasibility, biological basis, complications, and patient selection."
  ]
}